## ⚙️ Installation

### 1️⃣ Clone the repository

```
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
cd inventory-app
```

---

### 2️⃣ Backend Setup

```
cd backend
npm install
npm start
```

Server runs on:

```
http://localhost:5000
```

---

### 3️⃣ Frontend Setup

```
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Frontend runs on:

```
http://localhost:5173
```

---

## 🔗 API Endpoint

### Search API

```
GET /search
```

### Query Params

| Param    | Type   | Example |
| -------- | ------ | ------- |
| q        | string | rice    |
| category | string | grain   |
| minPrice | number | 10      |
| maxPrice | number | 100     |

### Example:

```
/search?q=rice&category=grain&minPrice=10&maxPrice=100
```

---

## ⚠️ Important Notes

### ✅ Category values must match exactly:

```
grain
food
electronics
```

### ❌ Wrong:

```
Grain
FOOD
```

---

### ✅ Database Requirement

Make sure `category` field is NOT NULL.

Example:

```
{
  "product_name": "Rice Bag",
  "price": 50,
  "category": "grain"
}
```

---

## 🐞 Common Errors & Fixes

### 1. ❌ Invalid category

**Reason:**

* Category mismatch (case-sensitive)

**Fix:**

* Use lowercase values
* Or convert in frontend:

```
filters.category.toLowerCase()
```

---

### 2. ❌ No results found

**Reason:**

* Category is NULL in DB

**Fix:**

* Update DB category values

---

### 3. ❌ Failed to fetch / CORS

**Reason:**

* Backend not running or sleeping

**Fix:**

* Restart backend
* Add CORS:

```
app.use(cors());
```

